# Website Requirements Brief

**(Immigration & Regulated Services)**

---

**Organization Name:**
**Regulatory Domain:** Immigration / Global Mobility
**Prepared by:**
**Date:**
**Version:**

---

## 1. Regulatory Context & Business Overview

Describe the nature of immigration services offered and the jurisdictions involved.

* Type of services (information-only, consultation, case management, referrals, etc.)
* Countries / jurisdictions covered
* Nature of clients (individuals, families, businesses)

**Regulatory positioning:**
(Example: “The website provides informational content and consultation booking only and does not constitute legal advice.”)

---

## 2. Purpose of the Website

Clearly define what the website is allowed to do versus what it must not do.

**Primary objectives:**

* Lead generation / consultation booking
* Information dissemination
* Brand credibility and trust-building

**Explicit non-objectives:**

* Providing legal advice
* Case outcome guarantees
* Automated eligibility determinations (unless legally vetted)

---

## 3. Target Audience & Risk Sensitivity

Identify users with attention to vulnerability and compliance.

**Primary User:**
Individual / family seeking immigration guidance
Key concerns: legality, accuracy, confidentiality, cost transparency

**Secondary User:**
Business / employer / HR representative

**Risk note:**
Users may misinterpret information as legal advice—content and UX must actively prevent this.

---

## 4. Permitted User Journeys (Compliance-Aware)

Define journeys with regulatory guardrails.

**Journey 1: Information → Consultation**

* Entry via informational page
* Prominent disclaimer visible before CTAs
* Consultation booking with consent acknowledgement

**Journey 2: Business Inquiry**

* High-level service overview
* No jurisdiction-specific advice without consultation
* Structured inquiry form with limited data capture

---

## 5. Website Structure (Regulatory View)

Indicative sections:

* Home
* Services (high-level, non-advisory)
* Countries / Programs (informational only)
* Consultation Booking
* Disclaimers & Legal Notices
* Privacy Policy & Data Handling
* Contact

---

## 6. Functional Requirements (Regulated)

All features must support compliance and auditability.

* Consultation booking with explicit consent checkbox
* Forms with minimum necessary data collection
* Secure email notifications (no sensitive data in plain text)
* CMS with content approval workflow
* Role-based admin access

---

## 7. Content & Legal Safeguards

For every page:

* Page Name
* Informational purpose
* What it explicitly does not provide
* Mandatory disclaimer placement
* CTA wording constraints (e.g., “Explore options” vs “Check eligibility”)

**Content ownership:**

* Business owner
* Legal reviewer (if applicable)

---

## 8. Data Protection & Privacy Requirements

Critical section for immigration services.

* Types of personal data collected
* Data minimization principles
* Storage and retention approach
* User consent and acknowledgment
* Compliance with applicable laws (IT Act, DPDP Act, GDPR if applicable)

---

## 9. Design & Trust Signals

Design must signal credibility without promising outcomes.

* Professional, restrained visual tone
* No success rate claims unless substantiated
* Clear distinction between information and advice
* Visible privacy and disclaimer links

---

## 10. SEO & Marketing Constraints

* No misleading keywords (e.g., “guaranteed visa”)
* Content must align with regulatory language
* Paid ads and landing pages must mirror website disclaimers

---

## 11. Technical & Security Requirements

* SSL mandatory
* Secure hosting (region specified if required)
* Access logs and basic audit trail
* Regular backups and update policy

---

## 12. Assumptions & Constraints

* Website is not a substitute for licensed legal counsel
* Services may vary by jurisdiction
* Content subject to regulatory changes

---

## 13. Explicit Out of Scope

* Legal advice
* Case outcome predictions
* Automated decision-making without human review

---

## 14. Acceptance & Compliance Checklist

The website is acceptable only if:

* All disclaimers are present and visible
* Forms collect only approved data
* Content has been reviewed for regulatory risk
* Privacy and data policies are live and accessible

---

## 15. Approval & Accountability

**Business Owner:**
**Compliance / Legal Reviewer:**
**Implementation Partner:**
**Date:**
